[31m-## 🏗️ Architecture[m
[31m-[m
[31m-<details>[m
[31m-<summary><b>Click to expand full architecture breakdown</b></summary>[m
[31m-[m
[31m-**Frontend**[m
[31m-- Built with **Next.js 16** (App Router) and **React**, written entirely in **TypeScript** for type safety across components.[m
[31m-- Zone-based UI lets operators switch between gates, concourses, and exit ramps without losing context.[m
[31m-- Fully responsive layout styled with modern CSS, designed for both control-room monitors and staff mobile devices.[m
[31m-[m
[31m-**AI Layer**[m
[31m-- Crowd images are sent to the **Google Gemini API**, using its multimodal vision capabilities to interpret scene content directly (no separate object-detection model required).[m
[31m-- A structured prompt pipeline asks Gemini to reason step-by-step: identify density → detect hazards → assess risk → propose an action → draft messaging.[m
[31m-- Responses are parsed into structured JSON consumed by the dashboard UI.[m
[31m-[m
[31m-**Backend / API Routes**[m
[31m-- Next.js API routes handle image intake, Gemini API calls, and response formatting — keeping the Gemini API key server-side and never exposed to the client.[m
[31m-[m
[31m-**Deployment**[m
[31m-- Hosted on **Vercel**, taking advantage of serverless functions for the API layer and edge-optimized delivery for the frontend.[m
[31m-- Environment variables (like the Gemini API key) are managed securely through Vercel's project settings in production.[m
[31m-[m
[31m-</details>[m
